timelineItems.desc: The San Jose Earthquakes and Seattle Sounders FC will inaugurate Levi’s Stadium in San Francisco when the clubs meet Saturday evening before an NBC Sports Network audience.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: San Jose Earthquakes vs Seattle Sounders | August 2, 2014

timelineItems.comment: First Half begins.
Obafemi Martins (Seattle Sounders FC) wins a free kick in the attacking half.

Foul by Sam Cronin (San Jose Earthquakes).
Zach Scott (Seattle Sounders FC) wins a free kick in the defensive half.

timelineItems.desc: Foul by Victor Bernardez (San Jose Earthquakes).
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Victor Bernardez booked for a high elbow on Martins

timelineItems.comment: Leonardo González (Seattle Sounders FC) wins a free kick on the left wing.
Foul by Víctor Bernárdez (San Jose Earthquakes).
Match ends, San Jose Earthquakes 1, Seattle Sounders FC 0.
